## ⛳ Completion signal — REQUIRED LAST LINE (run_claude_job.sh reads this for Steve's Telegram alert)

After all other work and logging, the VERY LAST line of your output MUST be exactly one of:
- `ROUTINE_COMPLETE` — the audit ran and the report was written. NOTE: a 🔴 EXPOSED or ⚠️ HARDEN verdict is still `ROUTINE_COMPLETE` — the *audit itself* succeeded; the findings are the deliverable, not a routine failure.
- `ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE: <one-line reason>` — the audit could not run or was only partial (subagent returned `status: blocked-*` / `partial-*`, a path was inaccessible, or a step was skipped).

Do NOT echo the subagent's full report as your final output — your last line must be the bare sentinel and nothing after it (the wrapper reads only the parent's last line). Output nothing after that line. This line is how Steve gets a done / not-fully-done alert on Telegram.
